INSTALL

omp has only been tested on Linux, specifically Arch and Ubuntu.

NOTE: After installing the first time, you MUST run ompinit in
each user's home directory that want's to use omp.  This only
needs to be done once.

From Source:

  You need OCaml and the OTk library installed.  Arch users can use
  the AUR 'ocaml-otk' package.  Others can get it at
http://forge.ocamlcore.org/projects/otk

  ./configure
  make
  sudo make install

  Default installation tree is /usr/local which may be changed with
  a --prefix option to configure.
  Files are installed in PREFIX/bin, PREFIX/share/omp, and
  PREFIX/share/doc/omp, any or all of which may be changed.
  See "./configure -h" for available options.

  Read the message after ./install carefully.

From Binary Package:
  ./configure
  sudo make ./install

Upgrade Binary:
  Most upgrades are changes in the "omp" executable.  Backup your
  existing executable and copy the new one to the same place.  It
  is always a good idea to make a copy of your scorelist just in
  case some bug slipped in the new version.

Upgrade from Source:
  Build the upgrade from source as above and do the same as
  Upgrade Binary.
  
Read The Fine Manual!
